{"id": "1472556497983770737", "channel_id": "1471324648179372072", "type": 0, "author_id": "618475034465533954", "author_name": "silencio3507", "author_bot": false, "content": "I’ve been mulling over my opinion on this mode. At first, I didn't like it, then I started enjoying myself, and now I'm somewhere in the middle.\n\nIt doesn't feel like a 'new game mode'. As many people have said, it just feels like a longer Pdive. Also, some characters feel extremely gimped, while others feel way too OP. I love my Pollux, and he makes grinding this event much, much easier, but I'm not sure that was the intention, to have some characters that just cheese through the content while others suffer.\n\nThe lack of meaningful choices is also an issue. It's directly copied from the main game, which is already a problem there, but here, after going through the runs dozens of times, it just gets annoying. Especially when I get a choice between deleting a card to recover 0 HP (since I don't need healing) or taking a shitty relic and a symptom card. This is not good decision-making design. It just feels like picking whatever, because neither option is necessary or enticing.\n\nAt this point, I’ve completed over half of the hard/madness limited achievements. HSR is... okay. It's passable. I am at the point where I don't even feel like grinding it on auto because I have better things to do, but I will finish it on time. However, if this mode keeps repeating limited goals/achievements without a serious rework... Ouch.\n\nIdeally? This sort of mode should have completely reworked relics. They shouldn't be a copy-paste of what we have. They should be game-changing and allow you to build your run around them. I would love to see some upgrades to the cards etc.\n\nIf this were my dream mode, I would have it be something closer to the original Illusive Realm in WuWa, where even standard and limited characters get to shine because of individual buffs and upgrades. I assume it would be difficult to achieve in Morimens, but I still think there should be something buffing the units outside of the portraits.\n\nJust my opinion. Good luck to the devs.", "timestamp": "2026-02-15T11:33:47.896000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2026-02-15T11:43:20.222000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "❤️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 2}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1471324648179372072", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Train game mode improvement feedback", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1181168158678204497", "1361168939622727801"]}
